(2)Backend PRD
Product name

Waste Classification Backend Service

Purpose

Receive images from the ESP32-CAM, run AI-based waste classification, return the predicted category, and store detection results for dashboard visualization and analytics.

Goals
Accept image/video requests from the firmware.
Run object detection and classification.
Identify waste as plastic, metal, or organic.
Return the classification response quickly.
Store results for history and analytics.
Provide API endpoints for the frontend dashboard.
Users
Firmware device
Web dashboard
System administrator
AI model developer
Scope
In scope
API development
AI inference pipeline
Result storage
Device authentication
Dashboard data endpoints
Logging and monitoring
Out of scope
Servo hardware control
Physical sensor reading
Frontend UI rendering
Dataset collection tooling beyond storage hooks
Functional requirements
The backend shall expose an endpoint for receiving waste images or frames.
The backend shall preprocess incoming media before inference.
The backend shall run the waste detection model.
The backend shall classify each item into plastic, metal, or organic.
The backend shall return a prediction response to the device.
The backend shall store each detection event with timestamp, category, confidence, and image reference.
The backend shall expose endpoints for dashboard statistics.
The backend shall support device authentication or API keys.
The backend shall log inference failures and request errors.
The backend shall support future retraining feedback storage.
Non-functional requirements
Low inference latency.
Reliable API availability.
Secure request handling.
Scalable architecture for multiple bins.
Easy model replacement and versioning.
Proposed API endpoints
Device endpoints
POST /api/detect
Input: image/frame, device ID
Output: predicted class, confidence, optional bounding boxes
GET /api/health
Output: service status
Frontend endpoints
GET /api/detections
GET /api/stats/daily
GET /api/stats/category
GET /api/bins/status
Data model

Each detection record should include:

Detection ID
Device ID
Timestamp
Predicted category
Confidence score
Bounding box data
Image path or URL
Processing time
Status: success, failed, pending
AI pipeline
Receive image
Validate request
Preprocess image
Run detection model
Select top category
Return prediction
Save result
Error handling
Invalid image formats shall return a clear error.
Low confidence predictions shall be flagged.
Model failure shall return a safe fallback response.
Database write failure shall be logged and retried.
Acceptance criteria
The backend accepts image uploads successfully.
The backend returns a valid category for each request.
Detection results are stored in the database.
The dashboard can fetch live and historical results.
The backend remains stable under repeated requests.